@startuml r7-before
' ============================================================
' R7 Before -- VisualNetwork coupled to MainGUI
' ============================================================

skinparam defaultFontName Courier
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam nodesep 40
skinparam ranksep 30
skinparam dpi 150

skinparam class {
  BackgroundColor<<model>> #D8FFD8
  BorderColor<<model>> #44AA44
  BackgroundColor<<ui>> #E8E8FF
  BorderColor<<ui>> #6666AA
  BackgroundColor<<bad>> #FFE0E0
  BorderColor<<bad>> #CC4444
}

class VisualNetwork <<bad>> {
  <color:#CC4444><b>View-model with upward coupling</b></color>
  __
  - probNet: ProbNet
  - <color:#CC4444>mainGUI: MainGUI</color>
  __
  + afterEditExecutes(PNEdit)
  + afterUndoingEdit(PNEdit)
  + afterRedoingEdit(PNEdit)
  - refreshUI()
  ..
  <color:#CC4444>mainGUI.mainPanel</color>
  <color:#CC4444>  .getEditionToolBar()</color>
  <color:#CC4444>  .getUndoButton().setEnabled()</color>
  <color:#CC4444>  .getRedoButton().setEnabled()</color>
}

class MainGUI <<ui>> {
  mainPanel: MainPanel
}

class MainPanel <<ui>> {
  + getEditionToolBar()
}

class EditionToolBar <<ui>> {
  + getUndoButton()
  + getRedoButton()
}

class MainPanelMenuAssistant <<model>> {
  <b>Already handles undo/redo</b>
  __
  + undoableEditHappened()
  - updateUndoRedo(canUndo, canRedo)
  ..
  setOptionEnabled(UNDO, canUndo)
  setOptionEnabled(REDO, canRedo)
  <i>updates menus AND toolbars</i>
}

VisualNetwork -[#CC4444]-> MainGUI : <color:#CC4444>upward coupling</color>
MainGUI --> MainPanel
MainPanel --> EditionToolBar

note bottom of VisualNetwork
  View-model layer reaches up to
  UI layer to toggle toolbar buttons.
  This duplicates what
  MainPanelMenuAssistant already does.
end note

@enduml
